Primitive Data Types:-


| Data Type |        Size       | Default Value | Range / Values                                          | Represents                       | Example                          |
| :-------- | :---------------: | :-----------: | :------------------------------------------------------ | :------------------------------- | :------------------------------- |
| `byte`    |  1 Byte (8 bits)  |      `0`      | -128 to 127                                             | Small whole numbers              | `byte age = 25;`                 |
| `short`   | 2 Bytes (16 bits) |      `0`      | -32,768 to 32,767                                       | Small integer values             | `short marks = 32000;`           |
| `int`     | 4 Bytes (32 bits) |      `0`      | -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647                         | Whole numbers (Most Used)        | `int salary = 50000;`            |
| `long`    | 8 Bytes (64 bits) |      `0L`     | -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,372,036,854,775,807 | Very large integers              | `long population = 8000000000L;` |
| `float`   | 4 Bytes (32 bits) |     `0.0f`    | ±3.4028235E38 (≈6–7 decimal digits)                     | Decimal numbers (less precision) | `float pi = 3.14f;`              |
| `double`  | 8 Bytes (64 bits) |     `0.0d`    | ±1.7976931348623157E308 (≈15–16 decimal digits)         | Decimal numbers (more precision) | `double price = 999.99;`         |
| `char`    | 2 Bytes (16 bits) |   `'\u0000'`  | Unicode characters (`0` to `65,535`)                    | Single character                 | `char grade = 'A';`              |
| `boolean` |   JVM Dependent*  |    `false`    | `true` or `false`                                       | Logical values                   | `boolean isPassed = true;`       |
